  "text": "PRESENT is a popular lightweight cipher that has a key size of either 80 bits or 128 bits and a block size of 64 bits. PRESENT was designed to be implemented efficiently in hardware where it can be engineered to have a very low gate count (1570 GE, which is competitive with leading compact stream ciphers) and high speed for each block (32 clock cycles). The cipher consists of an SP network, comprising a four bit sbox and a permutation layer. There are 32 rounds and a key schedule is used to derive 32 round keys each of which is 64 bits long [CITATION_1] .",
